This paper discusses techniques for improving query performance in analytic databases, which are typically used in commercial, scientific, and medical domains. The paper specifically focuses on addressing the issue of data skew, which is a common feature of real-world datasets. Given this focus, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.DB (Databases). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
